{"word":"εὐρακύλων","slug":"εὐρακύλων","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>εὐραϰύλων, ωνος, ὁ</el></b> [a hybrid formation <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ fr.\">fr.</a> (<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὁ\">ὁ</a></el>) <el>εὖρος</el> ‘the east wind’ + <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> Aquilo (hence Vulgate rendering ‘euroaquilo’)] ‘a northeast wind called <el>εὐ</el>.’, <b>north-easter <a href='B:510 27:14'>Ac 27:14</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:εὐπροσωπέω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:εὑρέθην\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}